-approach calculations using default\ninput parameters of TALYS has been appreciably improved by using modified\noptical model potential (OMP), deformation, and level density parameters. The\nOMP parameters have been extracted from theoretical fits to available\nexperimental elastic/inelastic nucleon scattering angular distribution data by\nmeans of the coupled-channels reaction code OPTMAN. Experimental data for\nseveral new $\\gamma$-ray lines are also reported and discussed. The\nastrophysical implications of our results are emphasised.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Jan 2020 12:53:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-19"}
